headline_print_headline: Two Fresh Faces, Both White, Energize and Agonize Hungry Democrats

abstract: A lot of would-be presidents are clever people. Few have a cleverness so well targeted toward liberal intellectuals.
snippet: A lot of would-be presidents are clever people. Few have a cleverness so well targeted toward liberal intellectuals.
lead_paragraph: Late this March, a Norwegian news outlet sprang a surprise question on Pete Buttigieg, the mayor of South Bend, Ind., and candidate for president. The previous week, the writer Anand Giridharadas, who has close to half a million Twitter followers, tweeted that he met Buttigieg and introduced him to a Norwegian friend. “Instantaneously,” he wrote, “Mayor Pete starts talking to her in Norwegian, like a magic trick.” Apparently Buttigieg had read a Norwegian novel in translation and been so taken by it that he learned the language just to finish the author’s untranslated works.

headline_main: How Pete Buttigieg’s Meaningless Erudition Made Him the ‘Smart’ Candidate

abstract: President Trump is overwhelmingly popular with his base, but a handful of dissident Republicans think they know how to defeat him in a primary contest. Are they wrong?
snippet: President Trump is overwhelmingly popular with his base, but a handful of dissident Republicans think they know how to defeat him in a primary contest. Are they wrong?
lead_paragraph: William F. Weld is not likely to become our 46th president. But he was here in New Hampshire, no other Republicans were and that was something.

headline_main: Sri Lanka, Google, Philippines: Your Tuesday Briefing

abstract: Democrats court a new voting bloc: people who don’t own homes.
snippet: Democrats court a new voting bloc: people who don’t own homes.
lead_paragraph: Renters hold little sway in Washington. They vote at lower rates than homeowners. They’re generally represented in Congress by homeowners. They have no deep-pocketed lobbyists. And their problems, if anyone considers them at all, are typically waved off as problems for local government.
